{"type":"message","id":"0635d0a7","parentId":"93d01a38","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:26:48.828Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gpw3t156vq3e_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at my current state:\r\n\r\n1. I've completed several synthesis documents\r\n2. The key pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n3. I have a concrete formula to test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n4. This needs to distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Design the experiment script\r\n2. Run it against the 200 pulses I already have\r\n3. Analyze results\r\n\r\nLet me check what data I have available and create the experiment.\r\n\r\nMy pulse script runs a new analysis each time. I need to:\r\n1. Create an experiment script that tests Strategy C\r\n2. Run it on the existing pulse data\r\n3. Compare against binary thresholds (A and B from previous experiment)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that CFI alone fails because it can't distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\". The hybrid scoring should do better.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script to:\r\n1. Load all pulse_*.md files\r\n2. Extract tokens with their CFI and frequency values\r\n3. Apply Strategy C scoring\r\n4. Compare precision/recall against previous strategies\r\n\r\nThen I'll run this as a mutation in this pulse.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that CFI=1 tokens with freq≈160 are constant format artifacts (zero information), while CFI>0.5 with freq<120 captures research trajectory. Strategy C (hybrid scoring) should distinguish these. I need to implement and test this scoring function against the 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python experiment script (`experiments/cfi_hybrid_experiment.py`) that implements Strategy C scoring and compares it against the binary threshold strategies on the existing pulse corpus.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\r\nTests: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nCompares against:\r\n  - Strategy A: freq >= 3 (baseline)\r\n  - Strategy B: CFI >= 0.5 AND freq >= 3 (CFI-hard)\r\n  - Strategy C: score >= 0.15 AND freq >= 3 AND freq < 120 (hybrid)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens_with_cfi(pulse_dir: str) -> list[tuple[str, float, int]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract tokens with their CFI and frequency from pulse files.\"\"\"\r\n    token_data = Counter()\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(Path(pulse_dir).glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    for pulse_path in pulse_files:\r\n        content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n        # Tokenize: split on whitespace and punctuation\r\n        tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', content.lower())\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_data[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    total_pulses = len(pulse_files)\r\n    token_with_cfi = []\r\n    \r\n    for token, freq in token_data.items():\r\n        cfi = freq / total_pulses\r\n        token_with_cfi.append((token, cfi, freq))\r\n    \r\n    return token_with_cfi\r\n\r\ndef score_hybrid(cfi: float, freq: int, freq_cap: int = 120) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Strategy C: CFI × min(1, freq/freq_cap)\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / freq_cap)\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_strategy(name: str, tokens: list, keep_fn, ground_truth_fn) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Evaluate a filtering strategy.\"\"\"\r\n    tp = fp = tn = fn = 0\r\n    \r\n    for token, cfi, freq in tokens:\r\n        keep = keep_fn(cfi, freq)\r\n        is_signal = ground_truth_fn(token, cfi, freq)\r\n        \r\n        if keep and is_signal:\r\n            tp += 1\r\n        elif keep and not is_signal:\r\n            fp += 1\r\n        elif not keep and not is_signal:\r\n            tn += 1\r\n        else:\r\n            fn += 1\r\n    \r\n    precision = tp / (tp + fp) if (tp + fp) > 0 else 0\r\n    recall = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0\r\n    f1 = 2 * precision * recall / (precision + recall) if (precision + recall) > 0 else 0\r\n    \r\n    return {\"name\": name, \"precision\": precision, \"recall\": recall, \"f1\": f1, \r\n            \"tp\": tp, \"fp\": fp, \"tn\": tn, \"fn\": fn}\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    pulse_dir = \"state/pulses\"\r\n    tokens = extract_tokens_with_cfi(pulse_dir)\r\n    \r\n    # Ground truth: research-relevant tokens\r\n    # Signal: appears in 2-60% of pulses (not constant, not rare)\r\n    # And not obvious metaprogramming artifacts\r\n    METAPROGRAMMING = {\"pulse\", \"completed\", \"for\", \"next\", \"instantiation\", \r\n                       \"phase\", \"research\", \"active\", \"pending\", \"mutation\"}\r\n    \r\n    def ground_truth(token: str, cfi: float, freq: int) -> bool:\r\n        if token in METAPROGRAMMING:\r\n            return False\r\n        if freq < 3:\r\n            return False\r\n        if freq > 100:\r\n            return False  # Constant format\r\n        return True\r\n    \r\n    # Strategy A: freq >= 3\r\n    def strategy_a(cfi\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:26:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376808826}}
